4: To the Farlands! To the Prince!
7:
Hah-hah-hah! Good, good! Drink! Let us
have some life in this dreary place!
12:
Sure sounds like you're all having a
good time! I can't drink, but do you have
anything non-alcoholic on the menu?
17: What? You would refuse my wine?
20:
*sigh* Very well. Come, bring juice for
the boy! Something sweet enough
to enliven the spirits!
28:
Yes. The heirs to the throne of Nihil
command the Nine Noble Houses.
32:
I am fourteenth in line to that throne—
Razelt, of the House of Nialas. You owe
me your love and honor!
36:
Cool. I've never seen a prince before.
My name's Alk. Nice to meet you,
your highness!
41:
You are forward, but I like you the better
for it. Now, Alk! Eat and drink your fill!
45:
All shall order as they wish! We mustn't
let clouds on the horizon lessen our
enjoyment of today. A kingdom is sound
only when its people are content!
46:
Do not worry about payment!
My tutor will—
58:
Has he no heart? Wringing every coin
from my purse, before hanging me out
to dry!
63:
Honestly, I'd have been surprised if he
let you stay...
67:
In the Farlands, there is a tab for the
royal family... Well. It's time I found an
inn—one that extends credit to princes!
69: Oof... How thick can that skin get...
73:
What is it, little one? Do not lay your
soiled hands upon me... Lave them,
and then return.
78:
Oh... Hey. He, uh, doesn't have any
money right now, but maybe I can—
82:
Merchant. How much wheat can I buy
with this gem?
89:
Hah-hah-hah! Eat, little ones! Eat, until
your stomachs grow round as drums!
94:
Stop laughing and help! This line's not
getting any shorter!
99:
You would ask a prince to work?
How bold.
104:
Hey, you sure it was a good idea?
You know, turning ALL your jewels into
porridge?
108: Of course. I have no regrets.
110:
But you could've rented a room with
some of them.
120:
That's not what your face is saying!
You didn't think this through, did you?!
124: A prince's judgement must be swift!
127:
Yeah, but not swifter than thought.
Right now, you're as helpless as a stray
puppy.
131: I am no STRAY! I am merely... a wayfarer.
135:
With no place to stay! Unless your fancy
armor turns into a tent, tonight's going
to be rough!
141:
Enough. I can sleep well, knowing that
the people do not go hungry.
145:
But this isn't even your country. Aren't
the Farlands a long way off?
151:
Even abroad, it is a prince's duty to look
after the people.
153:
This land is ruled not by a king, but by
merchants. Its ways are different, but
that does not make them lesser.
155:
All countries—and all people—are
linked. If I ever wish to be king, I must
learn to honor my neighbors.
159:
...Um, your highness? If you're interested,
I might know a place you can stay...
165:
Hah-hah-hah! Here is a rare sight,
hidden even from kings!
169:
You're free to stay until you find your
tutor. That is, if you like it here...
172:
I do! This shall be my new base, from
whence I will wander into foreign lands!
175:
All right, then. Happy to have you with
us, Razelt.
177:
And I am glad to be here. Now, Alk. Lead
me to my castle!
182:
How funny would it be if I brought him
to the doghouse...
